Evaluation of the effects of oral water and low-density barium sulphate suspension on bowel appearance on FDG-PET/CT. The purpose of this study is to assess which of five bowel preparation regimes offers superior bowel distension and to assess if these regimes adversely affect FDG activity on PET/CT imaging. The study conformed to HIPAA regulations. Ninety patients were divided into five groups of 18 who received no oral contrast agent (group A) 900 ml of water orally (group B)